/-
K=5 Root Existence and Convergence Certificate

This file proves that for K=5 continual learning tasks, there exists an
optimal uniform stepsize γ* at which the cycle operator M₅ achieves its
minimum spectral radius ρ* = T₅(γ*)/2 < 1.

The proof follows the same IVT structure as UUID ba9525b6 (K=4 case),
generalised to the degree-8 discriminant polynomial P₈.

From UUID bda28350 (Abel-Ruffini wall):
  disc(M_K) = T_K(γ)² - 4·D_K(γ) = γ² · P_{2(K-1)}(γ)

For K=5: deg P₈ = 2(5-1) = 8. Abel-Ruffini: no radical formula exists.
But existence of a root is guaranteed by the IVT (Theorem below).

Structure:
  Section 1: Abstract IVT for continuous functions (polynomial case)
  Section 2: Discriminant properties at endpoints γ=0 and γ=γ_NF
  Section 3: K=5 stability boundary γ_NF
  Section 4: K=5 root existence via IVT
  Section 5: Convergence certificate at γ*
  Section 6: Master K=5 theorem combining all results
-/

import Mathlib

set_option linter.mathlibStandardSet false

open scoped BigOperators
